<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gardner &amp; Champ" authorityYear="1849" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hamamelidaceae" genus="Eustigma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eustigma oblongifolium" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblongifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Eustigma oblongifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gardner &amp; Champ., but distinguished from that species by having entire elliptic to oblong leaves (vs. partly dentate oblong-lanceolate leaves), infructescences 5-10.3 cm long (vs. 3-5 cm long), apical part (above tepal scar) of capsules 6.5-9 mm long (vs. 3-5 mm long) and seed hilum 4 mm long and 3 mm wide for bigger side (vs. 2-3 mm long and 1-1.5 mm wide).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
